However, it&#39;s not doing what you think. There are two main problems with it:

1. Instead of getting the length of the session, you&#39;re getting the time from the end of the session since the beginning of the day. To fix this, use `totalTime = result.endDate.timeIntervalSince(result.startDate)`
2. The other problem I see is that you&#39;re calling `completion` *with the length of every session, **not the total time***. This may be what you want, but if it isn&#39;t, change the inside of your query to this:
```swift
if error != nil {
    print(&quot; HealthKit returned error while trying to query today&#39;s mindful sessions. The error was: \(error?.localizedDescription)&quot;)
}
if let results = results {
    var totalTime = TimeInterval()
    for result in results {
        totalTime += result.endDate.timeIntervalSince(result.startDate)
    }
    completion(totalTime)
} else {
    completion(0)
}
```

This sums all the sessions before calling the completion handler.

Hope this helps!

